during the last decade of the  19th century  the city of monterrey gained access to the railroads which benefitted industry it was during this period that  josé eleuterio gonzález  founded the  colegio civil  an early effort to create a nonreligious university in monterrey he also founded the  hospital civil  which is now one of the best public hospitals in the northeast of mexico and serves as medical school support to the school of medicine of the  autonomous university of nuevo león uanl   vicente ferrara  founded the fundidora de fierro y acero de monterrey a steelproducing company that accelerated the already fast industrialization of the city and became one of the worlds biggest at its time
